inn1.comm: From round the wickets, comes a length-delivery, angling in, Gilchrist tries to whip it to on side and gets a inside-edge onto his pads. No ball though.
lands on a length, outside off, comes in, Gilchrist goes back, pushes the bat out, away from the body, makes contact and the ball rolls towards cover
And again. Whippy action gets the ball back in from outside off, Gilchrist gets behind the line and defends

Fab delivery. It swung in late from outside off and Gilchrist is beaten by the movement and is rapped on the pads - it was going down leg side and the ball went to left of gully. They rush for a quick single, a shy comes at the striker's end, misses but Hayden would have made it.
another one swinging in to the hips, they will get a leg bye
Slap! Couple of deliveries were swinging down the leg side and so he started this one from well outside off but it sat up for Gilchrist to cut it past point
closer to the off stump, fuller, pushed towards mid-off
Fullish, hint of inswing, driven towards mid-on for a quick single
Caressed away. Classy. Overpitched outside off stump, down came the bat in a lovely arc to meet the ball flush in the middle and it sped through extra cover.
slides on to the legs, Gilchrist works it past square-leg
That silly mid-off comes into play. nice strangling delivery on the off and middle, goes on straight, Hayden gets his bat down in a hurry, pushes it out to silly mid-off
Another probing delivery on the off and middle, full in length, Jabbed away, gets an outside-edge through gully, down to third man
on the middle and leg, turned to midwicket
another inswining delivery from round the wickets, full in length on the middle stump line, Hayden leans forward, works it to left of mid-on
Don't bowl there! Short and wide, Gilchrist earns his living from those deliveries. Cut away past point. Whack!
almost at the blockhole, on the middle stump line, dug out to the right of mid-off for a single.
128.2 kmph back of length delivery, swinging to the hips, tucked away to fine-leg with ease.
fuller, again touch of in swing, from that round the wicket angle, driven towards mid-off
Peter Borren makes an athletic stop at cover. Overpitched on the off and Gilchrist drilled it to Borren's right but a fine stop there.
full in length, on the middle, driven back to the bowler
on the middle and leg, worked to midwicket. The wicketkeeper is standing up to the stumps
gentle seam-up delivery on the legs, shovelled away towards square-leg
full and just outside off stump, Gilchrist leans forward, opens the bat-face, punches it to point
similar line, just outside off, pushed back to the bowler.
again from round the wickets, in the channel outside off, Hayden plonks his right foot out and shoulders arms
bends in from just outside off, on the middle stump line, Hayden leans forward, plays it inside-out to cover
almost-yorker, at the off stump line, Hayden stabs it away down the track
driveable length, just outside off, driven to cover
continues to get some swing. Bit too early in the trajectory though. Outside off stump, driven out to mid-off
lands on a length, just outside off stump, rushes through to the channel, left alone. It's a maiden over!
Smack! overpitched outside off and crashed to deep cover.
Whack! overpitched on the off stump line, knifed through the line, past the bowler!
leans forward, pushes a length-delivery to cover
fullish, on to the pads, flicked away but straight to short fine leg.
on the leg and middle, worked to midwicket
comes in from outside off - he has bowling that all morning, pushed to cover
Hayden had enough of the nagging line.  Walks down the track, takes a length-delivery from outside off and dispatches it to wide mid-on
fuller, on the middle stump line, turned to midwicket
in the zone outside off, left alone
bit short and outside off stump, swatted away to the left of cover who makes a half-stop
fullish, a low full toss in fact, driven to deep cover
full, straight, on the middle stump line, pushed out to mid-off
full in length, just outside off stump, driven powerfully to mid-off
Boom! Similar delivery actually but Gilchirst smokes it through the line. Swing of the arms and the ball flies over the bowler's head
This one flies over square-leg. Didn't execute the pick-up shot well but still enough wood on it to send it over towards long-leg. Couple of bounces and over the ropes.
slipping down the leg side, tucked behind square-leg
just outside off, pushed out to cover
Thrash! Short and Gilchrist swivles to pull it over midwicket. What a player!
fuller, just outside off, punched to cover
nice delivery. swings in from a length, cramps Gilchrist for room and he adjusts by shutting the bat-face and pushing it to the on side
overpitched outside off stump, creamed through deep cover
short of length, just outside off stump, cut to point
fullish, lands outside off stump line, Hayden forces it away to short cover

Whoosh! Driveable length on the off stump and Gilchrist just hit through the line. Thought it would go straight to mid-off but i need to check my eyesight. It whizzed past him and to the boundary. That's the 100th four of Gilchrist in World Cup cricket. Take a bow!

Dropped by Tim de Leede at deep midwicket! Wild swing across the line and it went up to the clouds. Down she came and Tim de Leede run backwards, got into a perfect position but couldn't hold on to it
101st WC boundary. Overpitched outside off and creamed through cover. Pure timing.
another four. It's raining boundaries here. Drifting down the leg side, flicked away fine.
turned to the leg side, Gilchrist runs in from the other end, Hayden sends him back and he just makes in time to beat the direct hit
Bosh! Short and Hayden pulls it over deep midwicket. Caught by a man from Boony Army! Pity for Holland that he was standing in the stands!
short of length, outside off stump, pushed to cover point
slower one on the middle stump line, defended away
lands outside off stump, comes in, punched to mid-on
on the middle stump line ,full in length, driven back to the bowler
similar length, line is towards off stump, pushed out to cover
Clubbed away! Short of length, just outside off stump and he swipes it across the line past short midwicket.
he is going for it, every delivery now. Another swing at a length-delivery, doesn't connect well, goes towards mid-on
Hayden falls going for the broke. Slow offcutter outside off stump, Hayden has one wild swing, and edges it to Borren at point.
another slow delivery on the middle stump line, driven to the bowler.
gets it straighter, on the middle stump line, driven to mid-on
full and on the middle stump line, turned to square-leg
There he goes. Overpitched on the legs, Ponting leans forward and whips it past midwicket
Another four. no surprise eh? On the stumps, Ponting goes down town. Drives straight down the ground

Short of length, on the off and middle stump line, Ponting shapes to pull but is beaten by the bounce and the pace. I mean lack of it. It didn't rise high nor did it come through. And it bounds off the pads to the backward point region
full and straight, on the middle and leg, driven to mid-on and he sets off for a single
slower offcutter, on the middle and off stump line, Gilchrist waits for it to arrive, guides it to point
fuller and faster, driven to mid-off
slower one on the middle and leg stump line, he is bowling a orgy of slower ones here, pushed out to mid-off.
Was it a another slower one? Hmm...  offcutter on the off stump, cut to point

Aha! another slower one. The orgy continues. And almost takes out Gilchrist who shapes to pull but is beaten by the change in pace. He is struck on the pad but going down. The cheeky keeper who had earlier yelled, "they don't like the kiwis' appeals, Bucknor turns it down
around off stump, driven to cover
length-delivery on the off stump line, pushed back to the bowler
similar line, nudged towards point. Good over so far.
low full toss, hint of swing in and Ponting pushes it tamely back to the bowler
Another low full toss and Ponting is no monk. He is not going to forgive your errors again and again. Whips it through midwicket.
I think he is the slower one specialist. His change of pace, i think, is the faster one! another slowish cutter, played to cover
there comes the change in pace, faster and slipping down the leg side, flicked away.
gentle seam-up stuff on the off and middle, pushed to cover
there comes the slower one. off cutter, driven to mid-off.
another slow off cutter, driven back to the bowler.
fullish, on the middle and leg, driven to long-on
overpitched on the legs, flicked away past square-leg. Don't bowl there boss. He will make you bleed.
better. length-delivery, just outside off stump, pushed to cover
Fifty up for Gilchrist. Short and on the middle and leg stump line, pulled away to deep midwicket
fuller and hint of inswing, on middle and leg, turned to square-leg
On the off stump line, coming in, Ricky Ponting pushes at it, gets a inside-edge on to he pads. They go up in appeal.
Oh ho! There goes Ponting. Probably he was enraged by the earlier appeal. He leans forward to swing it over long-on!
Slower one but Ponting picks it early, leans forward and sweeps it over square-leg.
outside off stump, shapes in, guided to point
fullish, around off stump line, driven powerfully but straight to cover
length-delivery on the middle stump line, Gilchrist whips it ,in the air, to the left of short midwicket who makes a neat stop
slightly short and outside off, cut to right of point where a diving half-stop is made
122.2 kmph, fuller and faster (compared to the previous deliveries), on the legs, runs off the pads as Ponting fails to get a touch
Wallop! Short and outside off, Gilchrist cuts it up and over point. No one home at deep point and he gets another boundary.
corrects his length, hurls this fuller, on the off stump, driven to mid-off

dropped by Zuiderant at midwicket! Fullish delivery, on the middle and leg, Ponting whips it hard but straight, at head-high, to Zuiderant who, I thought, had snaffled it but instead he clangs it. The ball bobbed out of his hand and he almost took it on the rebound and I think was about to throw it up in celebration, Gibbs style, when he lost control.  Oohs and aahs plus few curses, i am sure, would have emanated  from the Dutch fans.
length-delivery on the middle stump line, pushed back to the bowler.

Gilchrist is back into the hutch! Full in length, on the middle and leg stump line, driven uppishly straight to mid-on who makes no mistake. He holds on to it and only then throws the ball up in the air, unlike the earlier let off to Ponting.
leans forward, defends down the track
full in length, on the middle stump line, worked to midwicket
Wow what a fantastic catch by ten Doeschate! Ponting smashes a low full toss, low to the right of the bowler, who swoops down in a hurry to take the catch. Fab effort.
on the middle and leg, worked to backward square-leg
again worked through the backward square-leg area
another low full toss, on the middle stump, Clarke doesn't hit it straight back like Ponting, whips it towards mid-on
yorker! on the middle stump line, dug out back to the bowler
another one, almost at the blockhole, on the off stump line, jabbed away down the track. A fine over comes to an end.
slower one again. Defended off the front foot.
length-delivery, just outside off stump, run down to third man
full in length, lands just outside off, comes in a touch, pushed towards mid-on and Clarke sets off for a run
on the off and middle stump line, Hodge was a trifle early into his drive and it goes in the air but falls short of the bowler
on the middle and leg, worked to square-leg
back of length, just outside off stump, guided to third man region
beaten! probing delivery, outside off stump, hint of movement away and Hodge is sucked into a near-fatal drive.
slips down the leg side, 'keeper, standing up to the stumps, palms it away to fine leg
full and on the middle and leg, turned to midwicket
fullish, on the leg and middle, whipped to deep midwicket
full in length, driven back to the bowler
shout for lbw but going down. It landed on a length, on the middle stump line, veered towards leg, and rapped Hodge on the pad.
another wide down the leg side
classy off drive. Full-pitched outside off and he leant on to his drive. Placed it to left of mid-off. Purrfectly done.
slow off cutter on the off and middle, lapped past midwicket and they run hard to get three
huge shout for lbw. Full-pitched, just outside off stump, comes back in and beats the intended drive and raps him on the front pad. But point of impact was outside off stump.
short of length, outside off and cut past point. Fiesty shot.
fullish, on the middle, driven to mid-on
full , in the channel outside off, driven to mid-off
lands on a length, just outside off, guided to backward point
starts off with a no-ball. Floated on the off stump line, driven back to the bowler
Clarke does what he does best. Comes down the track to the spinner, drives to long on
Hodge stays where he is, just leans forward to drive to long on
lands outside off, turns in slightly, driven to long on. Can we pick some other spot please?
leans forward and defends.
And again. Ok if you want you can hit to long on... don't curb yourself.
nice loopy offspinning delivery, Hodge is almost beaten in the flight as he, I am sure wanted to drive to long on, drives it back down the track.
full in length, on the middle stump line, Clarke lunges forward, whips it to midwicket
slightly short of length, on the off stump line, Clarke shapes to cut, not much room there sir, and he ends up chopping it to the off side
will get a single this time, with a drive to left of mid-off
slightly short, just outside off stump, Hodge gets back and across to cut it past point
fuller, and around off stump, driven to cover
off cutter, fullish, turned straight to midwicket.
turns in from outside off stump. turned to the leg side.
on the middle and leg, turns in, played behind square-leg
flatter, on the off and middle stump line, punched to mid-on.
nice. Clarke charges out but Raja drags back the length and Clarke pushes it out towards midwicket
loopy delivery on the middle stump line, Clarke comes down again but can't get under the ball, turns it to midwicket. GOod bowling.
deja-vu. Excellent stuff from Raja.
homes in on the off stump line, nudged to point
length-delivery, on the middle stump line, whipped to midwicket.
wide down the leg side. Good work from the 'keeper who whips the bails off but Hodge had not gone anywhere
off cutter, on the middle stump line, turned with the spin to long leg
full-pitched on the middle stump line, driven to right of mid-on
homes in on the off stump, defended on the front foot
beaten! Another ambitious drive to a length-delivery outside off, bat meets thin air, ball goes into the 'keeper's gloves.
pushed through quickly on off and middle stump, Clarke pushes it in front of midwicket and scampers through for a sharp single
Hodge uses his feet to take the ball on the full, he drives it straight down the ground and with mid on adn mid off up in the circle that was always going to be four
flicked off his pads behind square for a single
Clarke hops down the track and plays it in front of midwicket for one more
full length ball drifting on to off and middle stump, Hodge leans across and taps it wide of midwicket
Clarke uses his feet to step down the track and nearly yorks himself, he manages to dig it out towards deep cover
full ball on middle and leg stump, Clarke flicks through midwicket for a single
played off the pads through square leg for one more
short ball and wide outside off stump, Clarke doesn't move his feet and reaches out for it, he cuts hard but can't beat point
full ball nearly in the blockhole outside off stump, Clarke plays it to cover
driven down to long on for a single
defended back to the bowler on the back foot
Clarke steps down the track and defends on the front foot
tossed up on off and middle stump, Clarke takes two steps down and works the ball through midwicket
Hodge closes the face of the bat and plays it wide of the fielder at midwicket for one more
and again he advances to Raja and drives him down the ground, Clarke does this really well against spin
Raja drifts on to leg stump and Hodge sweeps him but can't beat the man at short fine leg
pushed through midwicket on the front foot for a single to end the over
short of  alength ball outside off stump, Hodge stands on the back foot and cuts to point
good length ball on off stump, Hodge tries to swipe it through the leg side but mis-hits it back to the bowler
Borren bowls the slower ball and Hodge  gets deceived by the change of pace, he ends up scooping it over cover and the ball falls in no mans land
driven hard into the ground and back to the bowler
cut past point on the back foot, he's placed that superbly and third man has no chance in cutting that off
defended towards cover point on the front foot
defended to covers on the front foot
on the off and middle stump line, pushed back to the bowler.
Clarke goes down town. Charges out, didn't get to the pitch of the flighted delivery but he went through with the shot, up and over mid-on
on the off and middle, pushed to the bowler
comes down the track, drives a delivery to long-on
straighter one outside off, nudged to backward point
on the off and middle stump line, pushed to the on side
short and Hodge swivels to pull it to deep midwicket.
fuller and well outside off, Clarke reaches out for it like a greedy little boy would do for an ice cream and drives it to deep cover
Hodge lets the ball come to him and drives to mid-off.
just short of length, outside off stump, Hodge was committed on the front foot, waits and opens the bat-face to run it down to third man
fuller and on the off and middle, driven to mid-on but he had placed it gently and knew immediately that there was a single in it.
in the middle he comes down the track and drives to long-on
slightly short, cut to point
slower through the air, turns in from outside off, Clarke waits for it to arrive, nudges it close on the on side and rushes for a quick single
another nice loopy delivery - This Raja is a good spinner- pushed to cover for a single
Clarke comes down, Raja pushes it to the legs, driven down to long-on
on the off and middle stump line, punched down to long-on
length-delivery that comes in towards middle stump line, pushed to midwicket
Thwack! Full-pitched delivery outside off stump and Hodge knifes it over mid-off. A Aussie girl, in the crowd,  throws up an Kangaroo doll in the air in delight. Hmm...
driven past mid-off
slightly short, pulled to square-leg. Drinks.
nice strangling delivery on the off stump, pushed back to the bowler
Cute! arm-ball, outside off stump, slightly short and Clarke backs away and cuts it late. Very late.
turns in from outside off, Clarke nudges it to cover point for a single
nicely flighted, loops outside off stump, Hodge leans forward, drives to mid-off
long-hop from Raja who was bowling so well. Clarke pulls it away to the boundary. Easy pickings there. That 'roo doll must have been thrown up again.
tossed up on the middle stump line, driven to long on
overpitched outside off, driven to cover
leans forward, drives a full-pitched delivery, down to long-on
length-delivery on the off stump line, worked to the on side
another sliding delivery, on the middle stump line, punched on the up, towards long-on

length-delivery outside off, Hodge tries to drive it, gets an inside-edge. For a moment he didn't know where it went - the truth is always under your nose sir, turns in all directions and ah.. there it is .. just outside off stump.
slips down leg side, flicked to fine-leg
full-pitched, whipped throught midwicket region
overpitched outside off, driven to long-off
pinches a single with a drive to cover
another full in length, this time a single down to long on.
full and outside off stump, Hodge leans back and cuts it, not the length but he pulls it off, to wide third man
full and on the middle stump, another single to long-on. Both the batsmen on 49.
full and slips down the leg side, Hodge tries to get a tickle but fails
slower one outside off, Hodge reaches out and drives it back to the bowler
still on 49. Whips a full-pitched delivery to midwicket
slower one- leg break this time, Hodge reads it and reaches his first WC fifty with inside-out drive to sweeper cover
Clarke gets to the landmark as well. Leans forward, reaches a wide delivery outside off and creams it through extra cover
celebrates the fifty with a fierce punch through the line, past the bowler.
Clarke backs away, ball is hurled full and outside off and Clarke reaches out and smokes it through backward point. The slog overs are on and Stephenson could be in for a treat.
Gets Hodge on strike with a drive to long on
Hodge smashes a fullish delivery down the track, the bowler gets a hand, nearly deflects to the sticks - Clarke was out of his crease, and they will get a single
in the channel outside off stump, Clarke opens the bat-face , runs it for a single to backward point region
appeal for lbw but going down leg side. Full and sliding in  on to the legs, Hodge didnt' make contact with his swipe
ugly swipe across the line to deep midwicket
sliding on the leg stump line, he tries to lap it around the corner, doesn't make proper contact
low full-toss, swatted to long-on
another low full toss, slogged, again not much contact, to square-leg
The low full-tosses keep coming, dinked past square-leg
slower one, slipping down leg side, tickled to short fine-leg
length-delivery on the off stump, heaved away to long-on
tossed up outside off stump, Hodge reaches out and smashes it, in the air, over cover , one-bounce over the ropes.
Boom Boom! flighted delivery on the middle stump line, slog-sweeps it over deep midwicket. Caught by an Aussie fan in the crowd. Well done sir.
Minnow bashing is on. Low full-toss and Hodge clubs it away, deep into the midwicket stand.

Raja has got the yips, Another full toss and Hodge swatted it away towards left of long-on. Should have been caught butvan Bunge doesn't pick it up. He goes for it rather late and puts in a desperate dive but can't hold on.
The full-tosses keep coming. So does desperate dives in the out field. Heaved to long-off, van Troost tries his best to get under it, it just brushes his fingers as he dives forward.
full-pitched , driven to long-on
150 of the partnership comes up with a drive to long-on.
slower one ,from the back of the hand, jabbed away to cover
faster and full in length, drilled to long-on for a single.
the fine-leg is up in the circle but he hurls this one on the legs and Hodge makes him pay. Swings it to fine-leg boundary.
gentle seam-up delivery on the off stump line, driven to long-off.
Clean as a whistle! Flies over the Cow Corner. Took his left leg outside the line and hoicked it up and over.
rotates the strike with a single to midwicket
full and outside off, Clarke goes down on a bent knee, square-drives it to deep point
The cow corner is being peppered here. Another swing and up she went in the air, the fielder tries to get a hand and ends up palming it over the ropes.
on the middle and leg stump line, swung to long leg
corrects the line, gets it outside off and is driven to long-off
Clarke gets Hodge back on strike - he is on 98, with a nudge to backward point
Gets to his maiden ODI ton. Well done Hodge. Reached the landmark with a drive to wide long-off
Bosh! Took his left leg out of the line and swung a length-delivery to deep midwicket.
Wow! This one has disappeared over long-on. The assault is getting ferocious minute by minute. A fullish delivery outside off stump was swung over long-on.
Fullish, on the middle stump line, drilled to long--on
Nails another boundary. Another length-delivery has been imperiously dismissed over midwicket.
Non-violence follows violence. Same result though. Low full toss on the middle and leg stump line, and Hodge just flicked it away. Caressed it away to long leg boundary
back to swiping. Fetches a delivery from outside off and sends it past midwicket
Full-pitched on the middle and leg, driven back to the bowler
on the leg and middle stump line, heaved away to long leg
Huge huge shout for lbw as Clarke misses a low full-toss while trying to lap it to on side. Struck just outside the off stump and hence he survives.
Imperious. He walks down the track, ala Hayden, and swings a length-delivery over deep midwicket. The 'roo doll must be up in the clouds.

Hodge falls. What a knock it has been. A real blitz. The end came as he tried to go for another big one. A fullish delivery, on the off and middle stump line and Hodge shapes to swing it away, misses it completely and is cleaned up.
length-delivery on the off stump, punched through the line to long off
Clarke charges down the track and hits through the line of a length-delivery, down to long-on
slips down the leg side, Clarke tries to swing it away , misses and the ball runs off the pads to the off side
short of length, outside off stump, cut to deep point.
Hussey goes. He smashes a fullish delivery to long-on but couldn't clear the man at the deep. He had to go for it, just one more over left.
Wide down the leg side. Deflected by the 'keeper
full-pitched on the off stump, driven to long-off
Clarke sends our friend Warren a reminder:-)  He slaps a length-delivery on the stumps over deep midwicket for his first six of the day.  Hodge had 7.
Watson imposes himself on the proceedings with a clean drive down the ground.
on the leg and middle, driven to long-on for a single. Clarke on strike now. Will he go another big hit?
Yes he does! For his second six of the day. Charges down the track and lofts a fullish delivery over long-on.
Another almighty swing and it has been deposited on the top of the roof! A low full toss and he biffed it over the cow corner. The cows are getting really bruised today.
Clarke attempts another massive heave, not much wood on leather and he will have to be contend with just a single. Over to Watson.
Watto finishes the innings off in style. Another Dutch full-toss, another brutal Aussie swing, again the cow corner has been peppered.

inn2.comm: a lovely inswinger to start off, almost squeezed through the bat and pad gap. Gets a inside-edge on to the pad.
lands on a length, bends back in , another inside-edge on to the pad. Bracken is homing in. Lethally.
puts bat to ball. Just outside off stump, pushed to the off side.
slants away in the channel outside off stump and left alone. Bracken will mix things up here.
lands on a length, comes in, dabbed away to the off side.
Bend it like Bracken. Another one that curved back in and thudded into the pad. Going down leg side though.
Almost cleans up with a late outswinger. It landed on the off stump line and shaped away, Reekers is squared-up by the movement and the ball whizzes past the outside edge, past the off stump.
Clipped away! Drifting on to the pads and forced off the back foot, past square-leg
What a cheeky shot! Length-delivery on the middle stump line, lapped away through midwicket.
bounces past the leg stump, banged in short, tries to pull it away but misses.
Another short pitched stuff, at the body, Reekers pivots to pull it to fine leg
peach of a delivery. Beautiful outswinger that curved away, a lame poke by Zuiderant.
again Bracken bends it back in, Reekers arrests his front foot movement and brings the bat around, pushes it to the on side
Reekers attempts to counterpunch. Charges at a length delivery and tries to swing it across but makes no contact

Ah! the good old inside-edge to fine leg boundary. The lemon cut. Fullish and outside off stump, Reekers, maybe expecting a short pitched delvery, stays where he is and then has a flash at it. The bat comes down late but he gets a lucky edge.
this one goes with the angle, left alone
full and a touch wide outside off stump, Reekers drives to mid-off
slashed away! Zuiderant frees his arms at the width offered and slashes it through backward point. McGrath gets around from widish third man to make a neat stop near the ropes.
full and straight, on the middle and leg, pushed to mid-on
rushes through the channel outside off, left alone
slips down the leg side. Wide called.
And again. Tait loses control again. That slingy action.
gets it right this time. Through the corridor outside off stump, left alone
And again. A touch wide and Zuiderant threatened a drive but resists the urge.
on to the legs again, runs off the pad for a run.
well outside off stump, Reekers chases it but can't reach it
top-edged over the outstretched hand of Gilchrist! Banged in short and Reekers pulls but is beaten by the pace.
leans forward, opens the bat-face, guides a length-delivery to cover point
full in length, on the middle stump line, driven to mid-on
Wow! He smacked that. Overpitched outside off and Zuiderant thrust his left foot out and creamed it through widish mid-off. Some shot that.
slower one, around off, pushed to cover
in the channel outside off, run down to third man
Whack! Full-pitched on the off and middle stump line, drilled on the up past the bowler. What a shot! Some statement of intent.
short of length, outside off stump, dabbed to third man
full in length, around off and middle, pushed out to cover region
goes back and across, and swat-pulls a length delivery just outside off to mid-on!
145.1 kmph,  banged in short and outside off, Reekers wants to send it out to cow corner but is beaten  by the extra bounce.
goes for a yorker, dabbed to square-leg. Diving stop there by Hodge and he has a shy at non-striker's end, if he had hit Reekers would have been a goner.
attempted yorker, on the off stump line, square-driven to point
Reekers is in some mood. He is not going to mess around. A length-delivery on middle and leg stump line has been forced away to long-leg. He shuffled across and lapped it around the corner
on the off stump line, on a length, pushed to the off side
Bracken strikes with a slower one! Slow off cutter, on middle and leg stump line, Reekers shaped to play it to the on side, get a leading edge to cover
beaten in the channel outside off. Goes with the angle.
